his family hasnt seen araik sukasyan 
since the earthquake destroyed his school a year ago but they 
speak of him celebrating his 13th birthday soon and hope a moscow 
psychic can tell them where 
we wait to find him alive said his mother galine weeping 
as she pulled out araiks school portrait she hopes publicity will 
bring word from someone who has taken him in if that happened 
the fourth grader vanished in the rubble of school no 9 along 
with more than 500 other people when the earthquake hit leninakan 
during school hours dec 7 1988 
authorities say it killed 25000 people but the armenian relief 
agency search says 20000 more still are missing including 2000 
children 
they are not counted on the list of the dead or on the list of 
those evacuated said ashot georgyan director of the search 
office in yerevan capital of soviet armenia he said he had no way 
of knowing how many of the 20000 were dead and how many were just 
separated from their families 
we are now continuing the search for children particularly 
orphans who were sent in groups to various points in the soviet 
union and are still there in sanatoriums and resorts georgyan 
said 
many parents like the sukasyans believe officials may have 
lost track of some evacuees 
larissa vagashakovna head of the moscow office of search said 
she had asked in vain for state television to show pictures of the 
missing children 
its impossible to forget the faces of these parents she 
said they havent found the corpse and they havent found the 
child where have they disappeared to 
araiks sister narina also was in school no 9 when it 
crumpled she escaped and when her mother came running from home 
narina cried momma i am alive but i cant find my brother 
for a month after the earthquake the sukasyan family watched 
workers claw through the concrete and dust that had been school no 
9 
searchers found the bodies or identifiable parts of bodies of 
420 students and 26 teachers there was no sign of 100 others 
including araik 
there were people where they found only one leg and 
identified the shoe or the skirt and they buried that said lida 
grigoryan a teacher at another school and a friend of the family 
the sukasyans searched hospitals opened every one of thousands 
of coffins at the cemetery and telephoned relief agencies in 
yerevan and moscow 
they found no sign of their son and cling to the hope that 
someone took him away 
in moscow there is a woman who can see where someone is by 
looking at his picture we hope she can help araiks mother 
said then she was worried again because reports say the psychics 
powers only work with an original photograph 
this is a copy she said staring at her sons young 
serious face 
