<TEXT>
borders to the west opened 
today and czechs and slovaks crossed over them by the thousands as 
their countrys communist authorities allowed the first 
unrestricted travel in decades 
maybe this is truly freedom said stanislaw balaz who drove 
through the bratislavaberg crossing with his wife and 14yearold 
daughter en route to vienna 42 miles away 
the new openborder policy took effect at midnight balazs car 
was among more than 100 lined up at the crossing when the 
czechoslovak and austrian border guards shook hands then opened 
the barrier at 1204 am 
czechoslovak border guards reported a relatively light flow of 
traffic at the 20 rail and road crossings to austria throughout the 
morning probably a reflection of today being a regular working 
day 
austrian border officials said about 900 czechoslovak cars had 
passed through the bratislavaberg crossing by noon 
at other crossings the number of czechoslovaks traveling to 
austria was much smaller 
instead of a storm just a breeze the austria press agency 
