a verdict in the case of abu talb and three other palestinians 
is expected dec 21 their trial ended nov 15 on charges of murder 
and attempted murder in four bombings in copenhagen amsterdam and 
stockholm in 1985 and 1986 
jamila mograbi who is divorced from abu talb but still lives 
with him denied he was involved in the pan am bombing but would 
not discuss the other charges 
we are short of money its obvious that my husband is not 
some kind of terrorist because terrorists have money she told 
the associated press 
abu talb is a former member of the palestine popular struggle 
front a group based in syria that rejects compromise with israel 
and opposes yasser arafat chief of the palestine liberation 
organization 
ahmed jibrils radical popular front for the liberation of 
palestinegeneral command is the group most often accused of the 
pan am attack 
ms mograbi said three scottish detectives and seven swedish 
officers searched the apartment last week for clothing traceable to 
malta in the mediterranean virtually emptying the closets and 
filling 15 plastic bags she said 
under swedish law evidence cannot be taken for a foreign 
investigation or removed from the country unless a court 
authorizes it 
investigators are said to have identified clothing originating 
in malta from the suitcase they believe contained the bomb 
they believe the bomb may have gone on an air malta flight to 
frankfurt where the pan am 103 originated the flight changed 
planes in london and was bound for new york 
ms mograbi 28 said abu talb brought three sweaters and a pair 
of jeans from malta in october 1988 she said they were wholesale 
samples he intended to show retailers with the idea of importing 
such clothing 
abu talb was looking for a new business after his video store 
failed she said adding that he went to malta to recover from a 
stab wound suffered in a quarrel 
police arrested abu talb in may along with two of miss 
mograbis brothers and a fourth palestinian in connection with the 
four bombings 
even if you are suspected of one crime it doesnt mean you 
committed another she said in the interview monday 
according to court documents abu talb came to sweden in 1986 on 
a false moroccan passport miss mograbi said the couple has lived 
in sweden for six years 
court records say abu talb was born in lebanon served in the 
egyptian army underwent military training in the soviet union 
deserted the army and fled to lebanon where he joined the 
palestine popular struggle front 
