<TEXT>
a blast of arctic air sent shivers as far south as florida on 
monday cracking low temperature records in cities across the 
south another cold front brought heavy rainfall to the pacific 
northwest 
almost the entire eastern half of the country recorded freezing 
temperatures overnight as stiff north winds blew cold air south out 
of canada readings dipped into the single digits in minnesota 
wisconsin upper michigan and the northern atlantic coast 
only southern louisiana and southern and central florida were 
able to hold the temperature above freezing in lakeland one of 
nine florida cities reporting new record lows for the date the low 
of 31 degrees was 8 degrees below the previous record for the date 
morning lows were in the 20s and 30s in the great plains and 
below 20 from eastern minnesota through the great lakes ohio 
valley and tennessee valley to the atlantic coast 
lows were in the 40s in south central texas and above 50 along 
the northern and central pacific coast and over parts of southern 
california and southern arizona 
temperatures dipped into the teens and single numbers across 
parts of the plateau and rocky mountain region the low for the 
nation monday morning was 4 degrees below zero at gunnison colo 
strong northerly winds ushering the arctic air into the 
northeast drove wind chill readings well below zero overnight a 
wind chill advisory remained in effect monday afternoon for the 
central highlands and western mountains of maine 
a storm warning was in effect for the coast of maine and new 
hampshire 
strong winds blew down the eastern slopes of the northern 
rockies and a high wind warning was posted for the upper 
yellowstone valley of montana winds gusted to 69 mph at 
livingston mont 
