rain along the washington and oregon coast heavier rainfall totals 
for the six hour period ending at 10 am pst included more than an 
inch at fort lewis wash and tacoma wash and nearly an inch at 
olympia wash and astoria ore 
astoria received more than 2 inches of rain during the 24 hours 
ending at 4 am pst 
there were snow showers over parts of the great lakes region and 
the upper ohio valley during the morning and early afternoon 
sunny skies and brisk southwest winds were helping temperatures 
warm into 50s and 60s in the southern and central plains and the 
strong winds along the eastern slopes of the northern rockies 
helped temperatures warm into the 40s and 50s in montana 
