criminal acts have been committed before criminal investigations 
have been completed thornburgh said 
thornburghs comments were directed at schumer and morrison 
in a session with reporters last week thornburgh bristled at 
the suggestion that the justice department was not aggressively 
pursuing an investigation of pierce because the two men sat 
together in president reagans cabinet 
let me tell this in this or any other case dick thornburgh 
is going to go where the evidence leads the attorney general 
said if the evidence is there we will take appropropriate 
action if its not we wont 
morrison suggested that thornburgh would not have ordered with 
preliminary inquiry without the request from the lawmakers saying 
there is no indication that it wouldnt have happened without our 
initiative 
