expected to last five days 
the federal leadership meanwhile said monday that a clash 
between slovenia and serbia two of its constituent republics 
seriously threatens yugoslav unity 
the statement from the nations eightmember state presidency 
was carried by the official tanjug news agency 
serbia cut all political and business contacts with slovenia 
last wednesday after authorities there banned a rally by serbs 
the presidency said without elaborating it will take all steps 
necessary to solve the worst political crisis in communist 
yugoslavias 46 years of existence 
it said the federations political situation has dangerously 
deteriorated because of the clash which seriously threatens 
yugoslavias integrity 
the yugoslav federation consists of six republics and two 
autonomous provinces encompassing varied ethnic groups and 
religions the latest row brought to a head a long series of bitter 
disputes between slovenia and serbia 
slovenias liberaloriented leadership advocates regional 
autonomy and has legalized opposition parties that are to contest 
the firstever free multiparty elections in postworld war ii 
yugoslavia scheduled for next march 
serbias leadership favors a centralized federation and opposes 
westernstyle political pluralism 
several serbian firms said monday they are severing all economic 
ties with slovenian firms and closing down branch offices there 
economists say cutting business ties will backfire since serbia 
is economically much weaker than slovenia 
yugoslavias political economic and social problems have 
mushroomed since the death in 1980 of president josip broz tito 
who founded the modern yugoslav federation in 1943 
