geraldine james had doubts about acting in the 
merchant of venice until she learned that her costar was dustin 
hoffman 
when i knew who was playing shylock i became rather keen to 
do it unsurprisingly says the 39yearold english actress 
fresh from a sellout london run as portia to hoffmans jewish 
moneylender in shakespeares dark comedy of caskets the law and 
revenge 
the production directed by sir peter hall marked hoffmans 
british and shakespearean stage debut and packed londons phoenix 
theater for 18 weeks 
the play is now on view at broadways 46th st theater for a 
limited engagement through feb 24 it gives americans the 
opportunity to see a twotime oscarwinner tackle shakespeare in a 
performance which james says changed nightly in london 
to do the trial scene i used to walk on every day not knowing 
what was going to happen she says referring to portias 
fourthact encounter with shylock the beleaguered and vengeful 
moneylender who meets his match in the heiress portia 
when dustin was truthful even if he took choices that were 
wrong he was always brilliant so riveting and unexpected she 
says 
i felt very protective of him the whole company as a 
company was so proud to be working with him he was so generous 
