shakespeares celebrated phrase the next 
its tempting to iron those contradictions out so that 
characters become onedimensional in order to become 
recognizable james says as actors we always want to be liked 
its much braver to dare to be disliked 
she says portias complexities are part of her interest 
people say how can someone be as nice and as nasty as 
portia but were very often like that james says its much 
too simple to say portias any one thing because shes all of them 
its important to win an audience around through convincing 
them of the truth of the character 
