<TEXT>
m danny wall under fire for his handling of 
what may become the costliest savings and loan failure in history 
resigned monday as the governments chief sampl regulator 
in his letter of resignation to president bush wall complained 
he was being made a scapegoat for the problems of the entire 
industry and denounced a steady stream of onesided information 
from congressional hearings concerning the collapse of lincoln 
savings and loan association of irvine calif 
rep henry b gonzalez dtexas chairman of the house banking 
committee has blamed wall for allowing lincoln to remain open 
until last april even though government examiners had recommended 
in may 1987 that it be closed the bailout of the institution is 
expected to cost taxpayers up to 25 billion 
in turn wall criticized gonzalez on monday saying he 
resorted to corruption of the truth in trying to force the 
regulator out 
walls departure brought expressions of relief from congress and 
the bush administration 
gonzalez said in a statement i know this was a difficult 
decision but i commend him for taking the action so that the air 
may be cleared and we may move forward in dealing with the savings 
and loan crisis he made no mention of walls accusations 
another committee member rep charles schumer dny said 
wall deserves to go but added that he should not be held as 
the scepagoat for the thrift mess 
walls mentor sen jake garn rutah who brought him to 
washington in 1975 as his chief aide said wall was a man of 
unquestionably solid character and integrity but was a 
convenient target for the critics who sought a scapegoat for the 
serious problems in the thrift industry 
treasury secretary nicholas f brady whose department oversees 
walls office of thrift supervision commended the regulators 
decision to step down as public spirited 
he added we are beginning the search for a new ots director 
and are committed to a smooth transition and the uninterrupted 
continuation of the agencys important work 
according to an industry source three candidates favored by the 
treasury department are richard f syron president of the federal 
reserve bank of boston william h roelle who is in charge of sampl 
rescue deals at the resolution trust corp and william taylor a 
senior regulatory official at the federal reserve board now serving 
as an adviser to the administration board that oversees the rtc 
wall set no firm date for his departure saying he would stay on 
for a transition period he said he was looking forward to a job 
out of government but had no specific position in mind 
for nearly two months wall has been the chief target of 
hearings by gonzalezs panel at first only gonzalez called for 
his resignation but in recent weeks the committee chairman was 
joined by senate majority leader george mitchell dmaine private 
groups and several major newspapers 
neither brady nor president bush defended wall in public and 
according to government sources white house counsel c boyden gray 
was pushing for his ouster wall however declared to a packed 
news conference this has been completely at my initiative 
wall said he had offered to leave office last january but the 
administration which at that time was drafting proposed sampl 
bailout legislation wanted him to serve out his term through june 
30 1991 
the investigation by the house banking committee has also 
stirred up trouble for five senators who intervened with regulators 
on lincolns behalf before wall took office july 1 1987 
as i testified under oath neither political influence nor 
lincolns charles keating affected my decision on lincoln wall 
said in his resignation letter nor for that matter have i ever 
made decisions for political reasons during my tenure as chairman 
and director 
the senate ethics committee is investigating whether the 
senators donald riegle dmich alan cranston dcalif dennis 
deconcini dariz john mccain rariz and john glenn dohio 
violated conflictofinterest rules in their dealings with keating 
a phoenix ariz millionaire who was instrumental in obtaining 
thousands of dollars in political contributions to them 
keating faces a federal grand jury investigation in los angeles 
and he is the target of a 11 billion fraud and racketeering suit 
brought by federal regulators 
none of the members of congress suggested wall personally 
profited from his lincoln decisions but rep bruce vento dminn 
a member of the house banking committee said monday that wall 
put politics first and good public policy second and used 
excessively bad judgment 
wall said the simplistic efforts to find a scapegoat to 
shoulder the blame for the entire thrift crisis led various critics 
to join in the hue and cry raised by the house banking committee 
chairman for my departure from office 
he said gonzalez resorted to corruption of the truth and 
abandonment of our historical devotion to fair play and due process 
in his effort to remove me from office 
wall testified for 10 hours before gonzalezs committee in late 
november after the committee had already conducted five allday 
sessions to hear from walls critics the regulator attacked what 
he called the deliberately lopsided presentation during the 
hearings 
